(10166, 362, 'apply_sfour_expands_0_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'How long will it take for me to get a home?'),
(10167, 362, '_apply_sfour_expands_0_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'field_5c44e3227c643'),
(10168, 362, 'apply_sfour_expands_0_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'The whole process from application to move in may take up to 18 months. There are many factors involved with getting your home: available land, sweat equity hours and willingness to partner.. We are committed to getting you in your home as quickly as possible and in return we appreciate your hard work and patience.'),
(10169, 362, '_apply_sfour_expands_0_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e3227c66a'),
(10170, 362, 'apply_sfour_expands_1_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'How does a Habitat mortgage work?'),
(10171, 362, '_apply_sfour_expands_1_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'field_5c44e3227c643'),
(10172, 362, 'apply_sfour_expands_1_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'Habitat’s home ownership program is unique in two ways: (1) We sell houses to our partner families at the cost of materials plus real estate without adding in profit; 2) We offer mortgages to buy the house without charging interest. The no-interest mortgage is significant because a loan from a commercial bank adds interest payments, which can more than doubles the “cost” of the home to the buyer.\r\n\r\nOur policy is that families should repay their mortgages as fast as they are able and an average mortgage is 15 years. Mortgages may be extended to 20 or even 25 years in order to keep payments affordable. There is no penalty to the buyer for paying off the mortgage ahead of schedule – though other restrictions may remain in place for the entire original mortgage period.'),
(10173, 362, '_apply_sfour_expands_1_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e3227c66a'),
(10174, 362, 'apply_sfour_expands_2_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'Do I get to choose where I live?'),
(10175, 362, '_apply_sfour_expands_2_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'field_5c44e3227c643'),
(10176, 362, 'apply_sfour_expands_2_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'Lots are offered as they become available. We have built homes in all parts of Bloomington, so there is no guarantee where your lot will be. You have the option of refusing the first lot offered to you, but you will be asked to reapply to the program if you turn down a second lot offering.'),
(10177, 362, '_apply_sfour_expands_2_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e3227c66a'),
(10178, 362, 'apply_sfour_expands_3_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'Who pays to build each house?'),
(10179, 362, '_apply_sfour_expands_3_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'field_5c44e3227c643'),
(10180, 362, 'apply_sfour_expands_3_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'We work with faith communities, businesses, and other organizations and individuals to sponsor the building of a house. Such sponsors contribute a fee that goes towards buying materials for the home and typically sponsoring organizations also volunteer skilled and unskilled workers to build alongside the homeowners on the house they sponsor. Once an affiliate has built 20 houses, the monthly mortgage payments from those 20 families are sufficient to build an additional house each year. Thus, as mortgage payments are recycled, homeowners also sponsor Habitat houses. Other funding comes from grants and individual donations.'),
(10181, 362, '_apply_sfour_expands_3_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e3227c66a'),
(10182, 362, 'apply_sfour_expands', '7'),
(10183, 362, '_apply_sfour_expands', 'field_5c44e3227b080'),
(10184, 362, 'apply_sthree_expands_3_apply_sthree_exapnds_title', 'Warranty Request Form'),
(10185, 362, '_apply_sthree_expands_3_apply_sthree_exapnds_title', 'field_5c44e22030797'),
(10186, 362, 'apply_sthree_expands_3_apply_sthree_exapnds_body', 'The Bloomington High School North (BHSN) chapter of Habitat for Humanity was founded in 1998 by students Josh Girvin and Joe Aamidor. It received official independent campus chapter status in 2000 and works in partnership with our affiliate.\r\n\r\nOne of the strongest chapters in the nation, they have co-sponsored a house every year since 2000. In 2017–2018 their 75 members raised nearly $40,000.\r\n\r\nThe Bloomington High School North (BHSN) chapter of Habitat for Humanity was founded in 1998 by students Josh Girvin and Joe Aamidor. It received official independent campus chapter status in 2000 and works in partnership with our affiliate.\r\n\r\nOne of the strongest chapters in the nation, they have co-sponsored a house every year since 2000. In 2017–2018 their 75 members raised nearly $40,000.'),
(10187, 362, '_apply_sthree_expands_3_apply_sthree_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e23230798'),
(10188, 362, 'apply_sfour_expands_4_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'How will I earn sweat equity hours?'),
(10189, 362, '_apply_sfour_expands_4_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'field_5c44e3227c643'),
(10190, 362, 'apply_sfour_expands_4_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'The primary way to earn sweat equity hours is by working at construction sites and at least half of your hours must be completed on site. Additional hours may be earned by working in our office, attending homeownership classes, helping at ReStore and attending special events. New ideas to earn sweat equity are always welcome but must be approved ahead of time by the appropriate committee or by our advisory board. At a minimum, each adult member must complete four hours a month. A friend may donate up to 50 hours towards a family’s sweat equity.'),
(10191, 362, '_apply_sfour_expands_4_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e3227c66a'),
(10192, 362, 'apply_sfour_expands_5_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'What are homeownership classes?'),
(10193, 362, '_apply_sfour_expands_5_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'field_5c44e3227c643'),
(10194, 362, 'apply_sfour_expands_5_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'An important part of preparing partner families for the responsibilities and potential pitfalls of homeownership are the classes that we provide. There are at least three series of classes on the topics of Habitat Philosophy and Partnership, Financial Planning, and Home Maintenance and Neighborhood Development. Partner families are expected to attend these classes (counted towards sweat equity hours).'),
(10195, 362, '_apply_sfour_expands_5_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e3227c66a'),
(10196, 362, 'apply_sfour_expands_6_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'How big will my house be?'),
