(10458, 366, 'apply_sfour_expands_4_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'The primary way to earn sweat equity hours is by working at construction sites and at least half of your hours must be completed on site. Additional hours may be earned by working in our office, attending homeownership classes, helping at ReStore and attending special events. New ideas to earn sweat equity are always welcome but must be approved ahead of time by the appropriate committee or by our advisory board. At a minimum, each adult member must complete four hours a month. A friend may donate up to 50 hours towards a family’s sweat equity.'),
(10459, 366, '_apply_sfour_expands_4_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e3227c66a'),
(10460, 366, 'apply_sfour_expands_5_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'What are homeownership classes?'),
(10461, 366, '_apply_sfour_expands_5_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'field_5c44e3227c643'),
(10462, 366, 'apply_sfour_expands_5_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'An important part of preparing partner families for the responsibilities and potential pitfalls of homeownership are the classes that we provide. There are at least three series of classes on the topics of Habitat Philosophy and Partnership, Financial Planning, and Home Maintenance and Neighborhood Development. Partner families are expected to attend these classes (counted towards sweat equity hours).'),
(10463, 366, '_apply_sfour_expands_5_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e3227c66a'),
(10464, 366, 'apply_sfour_expands_6_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'How big will my house be?'),
(10465, 366, '_apply_sfour_expands_6_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'field_5c44e3227c643') ;
INSERT INTO `wp_postmeta` ( `meta_id`, `post_id`, `meta_key`, `meta_value`) VALUES
(10466, 366, 'apply_sfour_expands_6_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'House size depends on the number of family members who will be living there. The following is the maximum square footage for each house size: 900 square feet for a two-bedroom house, 1070 square feet for a three bedroom house, 1230 square feet for a four-bedroom house, and 1400 square feet for a five-bedroom house. The square foot numbers describe living space not including stairwells, crawl space and exterior storage.'),
(10467, 366, '_apply_sfour_expands_6_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e3227c66a'),
(10468, 366, 'apply_sfour_expands', '7'),
(10469, 366, '_apply_sfour_expands', 'field_5c44e3227b080'),
(10470, 366, 'image_hero_banner', '332'),
(10471, 366, '_image_hero_banner', 'field_5c43ccbc4730b'),
(10472, 26, 'apply_sfour_expands_7_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'Floor Plan?'),
(10473, 26, '_apply_sfour_expands_7_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'field_5c44e3227c643'),
(10474, 26, 'apply_sfour_expands_7_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'The size of a Habitat house is determined by the number of family members. Habitat provides a standard floor plan for each size house, which might be adapted to meet special needs of the lot or particular considerations of the family. All adjustments to floor plans are minimal and there is no guarantee that we can meet all the desires of the family.'),
(10475, 26, '_apply_sfour_expands_7_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e3227c66a'),
(10476, 26, 'apply_sfour_expands_8_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'Customization?'),
(10477, 26, '_apply_sfour_expands_8_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'field_5c44e3227c643'),
(10478, 26, 'apply_sfour_expands_8_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'There are some customizable choices for your home. Every homeowner can choose at no cost:\r\n\r\nVinyl siding and exterior door colors.\r\nRoof shingle color.\r\nCountertop colors for kitchen.\r\nPhone and cable jack locations.\r\nCarpeting and vinyl flooring selection.\r\nIf possible, some minimal changes to the basic floor plan.'),
(10479, 26, '_apply_sfour_expands_8_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e3227c66a'),
(10480, 26, 'apply_sfour_expands_9_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'Customized Budget?'),
(10481, 26, '_apply_sfour_expands_9_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'field_5c44e3227c643'),
(10482, 26, 'apply_sfour_expands_9_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'In an effort to personalize and beautify the home while still staying true to Habitat’s mission of building simple, decent, affordable housing a family may choose to add custom options in combination up to $2000, which will be added to their mortgage. Examples of these options include: appliances, ceiling fans, landscaping, extra windows air conditioning, etc.'),
(10483, 26, '_apply_sfour_expands_9_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e3227c66a'),
(10484, 26, 'apply_sfour_expands_10_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'Green Homes?'),
(10485, 26, '_apply_sfour_expands_10_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'field_5c44e3227c643'),
(10486, 26, 'apply_sfour_expands_10_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'In a further effort to ensure affordable housing, we have focused on building energy efficient homes. All of our homes are up to Energy-Star standards, and we are making steady progress towards even higher levels of green certification. This commitment helps not only the environment, but it also helps create sustained energy savings for our partner families.\r\n\r\nYou may contact the office for a comprehensive list of house features.'),
(10487, 26, '_apply_sfour_expands_10_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e3227c66a'),
(10488, 26, 'apply_sfour_expands_11_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'Does my house come with any warranties?'),
(10489, 26, '_apply_sfour_expands_11_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'field_5c44e3227c643'),
(10490, 26, 'apply_sfour_expands_11_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'There is a one-year warranty on all work done by us. This warranty excludes damage resulting from wear and tear. There is also a one-year warranty on all subcontracted work such as plumbing, electrical, and heating and cooling.'),
(10491, 26, '_apply_sfour_expands_11_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e3227c66a'),
(10492, 26, 'apply_sfour_expands_12_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'What if I need or want to sell my house?'),
(10493, 26, '_apply_sfour_expands_12_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'field_5c44e3227c643'),
(10494, 26, 'apply_sfour_expands_12_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'We want to build homes for people to live in, not to sell and make a profit. We do have guidelines for selling your home that will be discussed during homeowner meetings.'),
(10495, 26, '_apply_sfour_expands_12_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e3227c66a'),
(10496, 367, 'image_hero_banner', '332'),
(10497, 367, '_image_hero_banner', 'field_5c43ccbc4730b'),
(10498, 367, 'apply_section_one_row_one_apply_section_one_row_one_text', 'Habitat for Humanity believes that all hard-working individuals and families should have access to the benefits and stability of homeownership. In this belief, we are committed to partnering with families to build simple, decent, and affordable housing.\r\n\r\nThe low cost of our homes is made possible by the exceptional support of our community. Building costs remain low thanks to impressive donations and generous volunteerism. These factors make it possible to sell our homes to accepted families with a 0% interest loan and at no profit.'),
(10499, 367, '_apply_section_one_row_one_apply_section_one_row_one_text', 'field_5c44de49b4a32'),
(10500, 367, 'apply_section_one_row_one_apply_section_one_row_one_image', '334'),
(10501, 367, '_apply_section_one_row_one_apply_section_one_row_one_image', 'field_5c44de64b4a33'),
(10502, 367, 'apply_section_one_row_one', ''),
(10503, 367, '_apply_section_one_row_one', 'field_5c44de40b4a31'),
(10504, 367, 'apply_section_one_row_two_apply_section_one_row_two_image', '335'),
(10505, 367, '_apply_section_one_row_two_apply_section_one_row_two_image', 'field_5c44df2d65f67'),
(10506, 367, 'apply_section_one_row_two_apply_section_one_row_two_text', 'If you or someone you know is interested in applying to be a homeowner through Habitat for Humanity, please consider our three criteria:\r\n\r\n1. Need for Housing\r\n2. Ability to Pay\r\n3. Willingness to Partner'),
(10507, 367, '_apply_section_one_row_two_apply_section_one_row_two_text', 'field_5c44df2d65f66'),
(10508, 367, 'apply_section_one_row_two', ''),
(10509, 367, '_apply_section_one_row_two', 'field_5c44df2d65f65'),
(10510, 367, 'apply_stwo_title', 'Overview of the Process for Buying a Habitat Home'),
(10511, 367, '_apply_stwo_title', 'field_5c44e0addce7c'),
(10512, 367, 'apply_stwo_body', 'After determining that you meet our three criteria, please attend one of our homeowner information meetings. Applications are available at the Habitat Office and at Homeowner Information Meetings. We will be accepting applications July 7 – 19.\r\n\r\nOur Family Selection Committee with then review your application and hold a home interview to determine your approval for homeownership.\r\n\r\nOnce approved, you will be asked to sign a Covenant Agreement and make a modest deposit toward your home.\r\n\r\nYou are then eligible to start earning sweat equity. At minimum, each adult family member will be required to complete ten hours per month. Often a build lot offering is based on sweat equity progress.\r\n\r\nOnce your family has enough sweat equity accrued, you will be offered a build lot, at which time you will start working on your own home’s progress!\r\n\r\n<strong>View our upcoming Homeownership Program Information Meetings.</strong>'),
(10513, 367, '_apply_stwo_body', 'field_5c44e0c5dce7d'),
(10514, 367, 'apply_stwo_footer_tagline', 'We are pledged to the letter and spirit of U.S. policy for the achievement of equal housing opportunity throughout the nation. We encourage and support an affirmative advertising and marketing program in which there are no barriers to obtaining housing because of race, color, religion, sex, handicap, familial status, national origin, age, marital status, sexual orientation, or sources of income.'),
(10515, 367, '_apply_stwo_footer_tagline', 'field_5c44e0d4dce7e'),
(10516, 367, 'apply_sthree_expands_0_apply_sthree_exapnds_title', 'How to Qualify'),
(10517, 367, '_apply_sthree_expands_0_apply_sthree_exapnds_title', 'field_5c44e22030797'),
(10518, 367, 'apply_sthree_expands_0_apply_sthree_exapnds_body', 'Need for Housing\r\nYou will be considered for a Habitat home if your present housing is not adequate, and if you are unable to obtain adequate housing through other conventional means.\r\n\r\nLack of adequate housing may include problems with the present structure; water, electrical or sewage service systems; heating system, hazardous substances, or failure to meet city property maintenance standards. You may also meet the need for housing qualification if you are living in an overcrowded or unaffordable situation. If you are living in subsidized or transitional housing, such as Section 8, you may qualify.\r\n\r\nAbility to Pay\r\nAs you will be buying your house from Habitat, you must demonstrate an ability to pay the monthly mortgage payment on your home.  This monthly payment includes mortgage, real estate taxes, and insurance payments.  We will help you to determine if this payment will jeopardize your ability to meet all your other family financial obligations and expenses.\r\n\r\nFamily Income\r\nYour income should fall within 25% to 80% of the county’s median income for you family size (see chart below). Additionally, you must have at least one year of stable income coming into your household.  We can include non-work related income such as food stamps, child support, TANF, Social Security, etc. as stable income if you can guarantee you will receive that income for the next three years.\r\n\r\n2017 Annual Income Guidelines\r\n[Table] \r\n\r\n2017 Monthly Income Guidelines\r\n[Table] \r\n\r\nCredit\r\nAll applicants will undergo a credit check. Because we are interested in your access to homeownership, we are not as strict in your credit review as a bank might be. If there has been a bankruptcy in your past, it needs to be discharged for at least a year and you must demonstrate improved credit since then. If you have a court judgment resulting in a fine or settlement that is still unpaid, the judgment must be paid off in full. You must have a reasonable level of debt, and medical bills will not be counted against you.\r\n\r\nWillingness to Participate as a Partner with Habitat\r\nOnce you have been selected to receive a home, you become a partner family. This partnership is a unique characteristic of our program in that you contribute to your ongoing eligibility through sweat equity. This means that each adult family member is responsible for completing 250 volunteer hours with our affiliate. This sweat equity hour requirement can be completed during site construction on current homes, in the our office, at the ReStore and by attending homeowner classes. Sweat Equity is a fun way to stay involved with both the Habitat community and the process of completing your future home.\r\n\r\nIf you meet the qualifications and would like more information about Habitat homeownership, attend our next Homeowner Information Session at our office.\r\n\r\nQuestions?\r\nContact Habitat’s Poverty Elimination Coordinator:\r\npec@monroecountyhabitat.org\r\n812-331-4069'),
(10519, 367, '_apply_sthree_expands_0_apply_sthree_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e23230798'),
(10520, 367, 'apply_sthree_expands_1_apply_sthree_exapnds_title', 'Homeowner Meetings'),
(10521, 367, '_apply_sthree_expands_1_apply_sthree_exapnds_title', 'field_5c44e22030797'),
(10522, 367, 'apply_sthree_expands_1_apply_sthree_exapnds_body', 'We will be accepting applications July 7 – 19.\r\n\r\nMeetings last one hour. Please call 331-4069 to find out if dates, times or location have changed. Please come on time.\r\n\r\n2019 Homeowner Information Meeting Dates:\r\n\r\n\r\nHabitat for Humanity of Monroe County, Inc. is a fair housing not-for-profit corporation. Habitat welcomes all potential homeowners regardless of race, religion, national origin, sex, marital or family status, or age.'),
(10523, 367, '_apply_sthree_expands_1_apply_sthree_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e23230798'),
(10524, 367, 'apply_sthree_expands_2_apply_sthree_exapnds_title', 'Scholarships'),
(10525, 367, '_apply_sthree_expands_2_apply_sthree_exapnds_title', 'field_5c44e22030797'),
(10526, 367, 'apply_sthree_expands_2_apply_sthree_exapnds_body', 'A home is just the beginning. While our mission at Habitat for Humanity is to end poverty housing in Monroe County through affordable housing, we also recognize that educational opportunities are inextricably linked to the same battle. It is our hope that with the stability of a Habitat home, homeowners and their children will find themselves reaching goals that they had previously never thought possible. As our homeowners strive to fulfill their personal goals, we are proud to offer a yearly scholarship to assist in their education.\r\n\r\nThe Hart & Home Scholarship is named in honor of Habitat volunteer Jennifer Hart, who demonstrates an exemplary spirit and commitment to a better Monroe County. Jennifer’s dedication has inspired a yearly gift of $2,500 to fund a college-bound or enrolled student from a Habitat home.\r\n\r\nPlease complete the form below and download the scholarship application for complete eligibility and application requirements. All eligible candidates are encouraged to apply.\r\n\r\nApplication Deadline: \r\nAward Notification: \r\n\r\nFor more information contact Rebecca, the Poverty Elimination Director: mankowski@monroecountyhabitat.org'),
(10527, 367, '_apply_sthree_expands_2_apply_sthree_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e23230798'),
(10528, 367, 'apply_sthree_expands', '4'),
(10529, 367, '_apply_sthree_expands', 'field_5c44e1e830796'),
(10530, 367, 'apply_sfour_expands_0_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'How long will it take for me to get a home?'),
(10531, 367, '_apply_sfour_expands_0_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'field_5c44e3227c643'),
(10532, 367, 'apply_sfour_expands_0_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'The whole process from application to move in may take up to 18 months. There are many factors involved with getting your home: available land, sweat equity hours and willingness to partner.. We are committed to getting you in your home as quickly as possible and in return we appreciate your hard work and patience.'),
(10533, 367, '_apply_sfour_expands_0_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e3227c66a'),
(10534, 367, 'apply_sfour_expands_1_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'How does a Habitat mortgage work?'),
(10535, 367, '_apply_sfour_expands_1_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'field_5c44e3227c643'),
(10536, 367, 'apply_sfour_expands_1_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'Habitat’s home ownership program is unique in two ways: (1) We sell houses to our partner families at the cost of materials plus real estate without adding in profit; 2) We offer mortgages to buy the house without charging interest. The no-interest mortgage is significant because a loan from a commercial bank adds interest payments, which can more than doubles the “cost” of the home to the buyer.\r\n\r\nOur policy is that families should repay their mortgages as fast as they are able and an average mortgage is 15 years. Mortgages may be extended to 20 or even 25 years in order to keep payments affordable. There is no penalty to the buyer for paying off the mortgage ahead of schedule – though other restrictions may remain in place for the entire original mortgage period.'),
(10537, 367, '_apply_sfour_expands_1_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e3227c66a'),
(10538, 367, 'apply_sfour_expands_2_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'Do I get to choose where I live?'),
(10539, 367, '_apply_sfour_expands_2_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'field_5c44e3227c643'),
(10540, 367, 'apply_sfour_expands_2_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'Lots are offered as they become available. We have built homes in all parts of Bloomington, so there is no guarantee where your lot will be. You have the option of refusing the first lot offered to you, but you will be asked to reapply to the program if you turn down a second lot offering.'),
(10541, 367, '_apply_sfour_expands_2_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e3227c66a'),
(10542, 367, 'apply_sfour_expands_3_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'Who pays to build each house?'),
(10543, 367, '_apply_sfour_expands_3_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'field_5c44e3227c643'),
(10544, 367, 'apply_sfour_expands_3_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'We work with faith communities, businesses, and other organizations and individuals to sponsor the building of a house. Such sponsors contribute a fee that goes towards buying materials for the home and typically sponsoring organizations also volunteer skilled and unskilled workers to build alongside the homeowners on the house they sponsor. Once an affiliate has built 20 houses, the monthly mortgage payments from those 20 families are sufficient to build an additional house each year. Thus, as mortgage payments are recycled, homeowners also sponsor Habitat houses. Other funding comes from grants and individual donations.'),
(10545, 367, '_apply_sfour_expands_3_apply_sfour_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e3227c66a'),
(10546, 367, 'apply_sfour_expands', '13'),
(10547, 367, '_apply_sfour_expands', 'field_5c44e3227b080'),
(10548, 367, 'apply_sthree_expands_3_apply_sthree_exapnds_title', 'Warranty Request Form'),
(10549, 367, '_apply_sthree_expands_3_apply_sthree_exapnds_title', 'field_5c44e22030797'),
(10550, 367, 'apply_sthree_expands_3_apply_sthree_exapnds_body', 'Please complete the form below to submit your warranty request.\r\n\r\nEnglish Form\r\nEn Espanol\r\n\r\nThere is a one-year warranty on all work done by Habitat. This warranty excludes damage resulting from wear and tear. There is also a one-year warranty on all subcontracted work such as plumbing, electrical, and heating and cooling.\r\n\r\nIf a problem arises within the one-year warranty period involving work done by Habitat, the homeowner must submit a Warranty Request Form to the Habitat Director of Construction. The grievance must be addressed by the Director of Construction within seven days and will be followed by a written agreement detailing the solution and date by which the problem will be fixed. If the Director of Construction does not address a grievance within the allotted amount of time, the homeowner should contact the Family Services Director. The Family Services Director will review the actions taken by the Construction Supervisor and a response will be issued to the homeowner.\r\n\r\nRemember that in order for the problem to be properly addressed, you must submit a Warranty Request Form. If there is a problem with subcontracted work, the subcontractor is to be contacted directly by the homeowner.\r\n'),
(10551, 367, '_apply_sthree_expands_3_apply_sthree_exapnds_body', 'field_5c44e23230798'),
(10552, 367, 'apply_sfour_expands_4_apply_sfour_exapnds_title', 'How will I earn sweat equity hours?'),
